<h2>Guidelines</h2>
<h3>Where to use</h3>
<p>Separators are useful in menus, toolbars, and <a href="rules">written content</a>.</p>
<p>Avoid using too many separators. Font size, font weight, whitespace, color contrast and other visual characteristics are usually enough to create the needed distinction between elements.</p>
<h3 id="a11y">Accessibility</h3>
<p>The hr element has an implicit <code>role="separator"</code>. Do not add it. There is also no need to set <code>aria-orientation="horizontal"</code> since it is the default for hr.</p>
